{% block Alternatives %}
<div class="solution">
    <div class="card">
        <h3>Custom Breadcrumb ("symbol")</h3>
        <p>
            <mark class="subhead strong">When to use</mark>
            If your team has source-level control over UI code,
            but DOES have a hard requirement not provided by native HTML,
            you may choose to build a custom Breadcrumb.
            Or perhaps your legacy component has been flagged for remediation
            and you need a high quality reference.
            This custom example recreates the accessibility built into the
            NYSDS Breadcrumbs.
        </p>
        <p>
            <mark class="subhead strong">How is it different</mark>
            This Breadcrumb expresses the look-and-feel of the design system with most aspects
            modeled after the NYSDS Tab component.
            The concept of "collapsed links," and the implementation of a "revealer" button to show them,
            differentiate this Breadcrumb from a simple list of links.
            The significant accessibility implications of this design choice are discussed in
            <a href="#about-this-pattern">About this pattern</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
            <mark class="subhead strong">About the first demo</mark>
            On this page there are two demos of the same component.
            A "Reveal links/Collapse links" button is provided to reset each demo when playing with it.
            This button is <em>not</em> part of the Breadcrumb component.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                This first Breadcrumb provides a "symbol" appearance (three dots "...") for the revealer button,
                which has the addressable <code>aria-label</code> "show more links"
            </li>
            <li>
                It terminates with the non-linked "current page"
            </li>
            <li>
                It gains an accessible name by being <code>aria-labelledby</code> the <code>h4</code> heading above it,
                which also provides a visually hidden context hint
            </li>
        </ul>
        {% include "partials/a11y-rely-checks.njk" %}
    </div>

    {% block HTMLNative %}
    {% set preview %}
<div class="breadcrumb-demo">
    <h4 id="some-page-header">
        Department of Environmental Conservation
        <span class="sr-only">path to this page</span>
    </h4>
    <button aria-controls="symbol">Reveal links</button>

    <!-- Breadcrumb "symbol" -->
    <nav
        aria-labelledby="some-page-header"
        class="nysa11y breadcrumb"
        data-component="breadcrumb"
        data-revealer="symbol"
        data-html="custom"
        data-state="min"
        id="symbol">
        <ol>
            <li>
                <a href="https://dec.ny.gov/">Home</a>
            </li>
            <li data-part="revealer">
                <button class="revealer" aria-label="show more links"></button>
            </li>
            <li class="intermediate">
                <a href="https://dec.ny.gov/environmental-protection">
                    Environmental Protection
                </a>
            </li>
            <li class="intermediate">
                <a href="https://dec.ny.gov/environmental-protection/water">
                    Water
                </a>
            </li>
            <li class="intermediate">
                <a href="https://dec.ny.gov/environmental-protection/water/water-quality">
                    Water Quality Management
                </a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="https://dec.ny.gov/environmental-protection/water/water-quality/stormwater">
                    Stormwater
                </a>
            </li>
            <li>Construction Stormwater Toolbox</li>
        </ol>
    </nav>
</div>
